The park itself becomes the game map.

⸻

IMMERSIVE ENTRY SYSTEM

HM-Based Access Mechanics

Even entering areas becomes gameplay.

Examples:

CUT Gates

Large jungle vines block pathways.
Guests must scan a digital HM badge or complete a challenge to “Cut” through.

The vines mechanically separate.

⸻

ROCK SMASH Areas

Guests activate interactive hammer stations to break glowing “rocks” that open hidden paths.

⸻

SURF Zones

Boat rides and moving water pathways unlock access to island habitats.

⸻

STRENGTH Puzzles

Collaborative physical puzzle rooms move giant blocks to open secret areas.

⸻

FLASH Caves

Dark bioluminescent caves illuminate only when guests activate their trainer devices.

⸻

SECRET AREAS

Some areas only unlock:

* at night
* during rain
* after catching certain Pokémon
* after gym completion
* during seasonal events

This creates:
exploration obsession and repeat visits.

